13/10/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- State prosecutors on Tuesday (October 12th) opened a criminal investigation against Mladen Obradovic, leader of the ultranationalist group Obraz, for violent conduct during clashes with police Sunday, coinciding with the Gay Pride Parade in Belgrade. Obradovic is believed to have orchestrated the anti-gay protests that injured more than 140 police officers. Prosecutors said they are investigating 134 other people for alleged involvement in the riots. In all, nearly 250 people were detained during and after the violence, which caused significant property damage. (Tanjug, RTS, AP - 12/10/10)
